When the new JIRA side bar is enabled, the buttons to navigate to Plan and Work Mode are missing which causing users unable to see their backlog/active sprints.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-11626].
  {panel}

JIRA date-time configuration is 'dd/MM/yyyy hh:mm', but in Sprint header there is another format used (with am-pm).

Customer noticed this in JIRA Agile:
{quote}
There is a minor bug in JIRA Agile which states "...Show less" after the lisf of filters in the JIRA Agile board but it should be "...Show fewer" because the list of filters is countable.
{quote}

It should be great if we can change the text to the appropriated word.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-11556].
  {panel}

As a user, I would like to be able search by the values in the "Epic Link" field from the _basic_ mode in the issue navigator.

At the moment, this is not supported and I am prompted to use _advanced_ search instead.

At the moment, the [Creating a Sprint|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/AGILE/Creating+a+Sprint] states under the 'Why can't I create a Sprint?' header:
{quote}An active sprint already exists: You cannot create a new sprint, if you have already started one. If you would like to have more than one active sprint at a time, please enable 'Parallel Sprints' in Labs.{quote}

This isn't the case. Without parallel sprints, more sprints cannot be started, but multiple planned sprints can be created.
